    "Description": "An update for kernel package is now avaiable for Anolis OS 8 that fix CVE-2022-2639:\n\nCVE-2022-2639:\nAn integer coercion error was found in the openvswitch kernel module. Given a sufficiently large number of actions, while copying and reserving memory for a new action of a new flow, the reserve_sfa_size() function does not return -EMSGSIZE as expected, potentially leading to an out-of-bounds write access. This flaw allows a local user to crash or potentially escalate their privileges on the system.",
    "Advisory": {
      "Severity": "Important",
